73. Cache Behavior and Locality Analysis
======================================================================

--- Cache Access Pattern Performance ---

| Size | Sequential | Strided | Random | Coalesced | Scattered |
|------|------------|---------|--------|-----------|-----------|
| 4096 | 0.53 | 0.58 | 0.52 | 0.16 | 0.57 |
| 16384 | 2.07 | 1.97 | 1.67 | 0.55 | 2.14 |
| 65536 | 4.94 | 5.11 | 3.75 | 2.24 | 7.03 |

--- Locality Comparison ---
Temporal Reuse: 2.27 M/s
Shared Memory Cached: 2.34 M/s
Speedup from explicit caching: 1.03x

--- Cache Efficiency Analysis ---
Sequential > Strided: sequential exploits spatial locality
Coalesced > Scattered: adjacent threads access adjacent memory
Temporal reuse benefits repeated access to same data
Shared memory provides explicit caching for frequently accessed data

--- Key Insights ---
1. Sequential access best: exploits cache line prefetch (spatial locality)
2. Strided access wastes bandwidth: skips most of each cache line
3. Random access worst: constant cache misses, no locality benefit
4. Coalesced float4 access: optimal thread cooperation
5. Shared memory as explicit cache can significantly speed up repeated access

