======================================================================
84. Shared Event Synchronization
======================================================================

--- GPU Signal and CPU Wait ---
CPU waited for GPU signal: 0.35 ms (signaled: true)

--- Shared Event Features ---
| Feature | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| makeSharedEvent | Creates event visible to CPU and GPU |
| encodeSignalEvent | GPU encodes signal into command buffer |
| waitUntilSignaled | CPU blocks until event is signaled |
| getCompletedValue | Query event state without blocking |
| GPU signals, CPU waits | Pattern for batch processing notification |

--- Key Insights ---
1. MTLSharedEvent enables GPU-to-CPU synchronization
2. GPU signals when command buffer completes via encodeSignalEvent
3. CPU waits for GPU completion using waitUntilSignaled
4. getCompletedValue allows polling without blocking
5. Shared events work across multiple GPU command queues
6. Use for: batch completion notification, pipeline synchronization

